= xdebug_call_file
Returns the calling file, or <code>NULL</code> if the stack frame does not exist
string
[int $depth = 1]
FUNC_BASIC

TXT:
This function returns the filename from where the current function/method
was executed from.

TXT:
To retrieve information from earlier stack frames, use the optional
<code>$depth</code> argument.

TXT:
For examples and more extensive information, see [FUNC:xdebug_call_class].
